# Deduplication

When the same transformation, validation, or mapping appears in two or more places, extract a shared helper and parameterize only what differs.

- ✅ Good:

  ```typescript
  const getAmenityLabelsFromOptions = (options?: Option[]) => {
    if (!options?.length) return []

    const labels = options
      .map((option) => getAmenityNameFromLabel(option.label.trim()))
      .filter((label): label is string => Boolean(label))

    return labels
  }

  const getMultiselectSegmentFromAmenityOptions = (
    options?: Option[],
    formatText?: (joinedOptions: string) => string,
  ) => createMultiselectSegment(getAmenityLabelsFromOptions(options), formatText)

  const formatRangeWithFormatter = (min: number, max: number, format: (value: number) => string) => {
    if (min === max) return format(min)

    const rangeValue = `${format(min)}-${format(max)}`
    return rangeValue
  }

  const formatRangeValue = (min: number, max: number) => formatRangeWithFormatter(min, max, String)
  const formatIntegerRangeValue = (min: number, max: number) =>
    formatRangeWithFormatter(min, max, formatIntegerPtBr)
  ```

- ❌ Bad:

  ```typescript
  const getDesiredAmenitiesSegment = (options?: Option[]) => {
    if (!options?.length) return null

    const labels = options
      .map((option) => getAmenityNameFromLabel(option.label.trim()))
      .filter((label): label is string => Boolean(label))

    return createMultiselectSegment(labels)
  }

  const getUndesiredAmenitiesSegment = (options?: Option[]) => {
    if (!options?.length) return null

    const labels = options
      .map((option) => getAmenityNameFromLabel(option.label.trim()))
      .filter((label): label is string => Boolean(label))

    return createMultiselectSegment(labels, (joined) => `Não desejado: ${joined}`)
  }
  ```

### When to extract

- The same block of logic is copied with only labels, templates, or formatters changing
- A reviewer flags duplicated mapping, filtering, or formatting
- Two functions would need the same fix if the shared behavior changes

### How to extract

- Name the helper after the shared concern, not one call site
- Pass differences as parameters: formatters, templates, predicates, or config keys
- Keep call-site wrappers thin when they only supply a label or template
